Aba Land Lords Protection and Development Associa­tion, (ALPADA) has given all its tenants 30 days within which they must get their Permanent Voters’ Card (PVCs) or face a process of ejection from their houses. The landlords gave this as a condition for retainaship as tenants in their houses in a communiqué issued recently at the end of their three days intensive deliberation, serious interactive sessions, workshops and membership training activ­ities tagged ALPADA WEEK. They said the measure was aimed at ensuring that voters were equipped with PVCs which is the most nec­essary material for a hitch-free election in 2023. -Advertisement- The association appreciat­ed Governor Okezie Ikpeazu’s efforts in infrastructural de­velopment of Aba in particu­lar, adding that his construc­tion of Echefu Road, Ibadan Street, Ngwa Road, Ukaegbu Road, Ehere Road and others under construction àt the moment had alleviated the sufferings of Aba residents.